4 Primitive Predicates
**********************

The interpreter provides an equality predicate with infix notation.
Two terms are equal if both terms are the same constant, or one is a
constant and the other is a variable.

     > 1 = 2?
     > 1 = 1?
     1 = 1.
     > X = 1?
     1 = 1.
     > X = X?


